          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>CARA 2.0 Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>This bill reauthorizes through FY2023 and revises several programs relating to opioid- and substance-use disorder prevention and treatment, including awareness campaigns and training programs for first responders; the bill also establishes several requirements relating to opioid prescribing practices, such as an initial three-day supply limit for certain opioids.</p>]]></text>
